is season to take take on Texas Tech for three games. First pitch on Friday is set for 7:30 p.m. ET, Saturday for 3 p.m. ET, and Sunday for 2 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_TexasTech.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_TexasTech.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs Texas Tech</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_TexasTech.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 9 Apr 2026 16:46:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58983</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Earns Fourth FWAA “Super 11” Honor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/football-wvu-earns-fourth-fwaa-super-11-honor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/football-wvu-earns-fourth-fwaa-super-11-honor</guid><category>Football, Athletics Communications</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2025-Super11" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" /><br /><br />DALLAS – One first-time winner and 10 previous ones, including West Virginia University for the second time in a row and fourth time in the past six years, comprise the 17th Super 11 Awards, presented annually by the Football Writers Association of America to the best performing College Sports Communicators departments in the NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision. The awards announced this week are for the 2025 season.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG"><media:title>2025-Super11</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 9 Apr 2026 12:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58981</s:story_id></item><item><title>Tennis Host No. 36 Houston, No. 18 UCF to Close Regular Season</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/tennis-host-no-41-houston-no-24-ucf-to-close-regular-season</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/tennis-host-no-41-houston-no-24-ucf-to-close-regular-season</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Zuzana Kudlackova" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/9/WVB00274.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (7-11, 1-10 Big 12) closes out the regular season at home this weekend with a pair of Big 12 matchups, hosting No. 36 Houston (16-5, 6-5 Big 12) on Friday, April 10, at 5 p.m., before welcoming No. 18 UCF (16-3, 9-2 Big 12) on Sunday, April 12, at 10 a.m. for Senior Day.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/WVB00274.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/WVB00274.jpg"><media:title>Zuzana Kudlackova</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/WVB00274.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 9 Apr 2026 15:14:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:spor