jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team earned its second win this season against in-state rival Marshall with a 12-2 victory in eight innings, Wednesday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 22-7 while the Thundering Herd fall to 14-17.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg"><media:title>Ian Korn</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 8 Apr 2026 23:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58979</s:story_id></item><item><title>Sixth Mountaineer Gear Sale to Take Place at Gold-Blue Spring Festival</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/football-sixth-mountaineer-gear-sale-to-take-place-at-gold-blue-spring-festival</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/football-sixth-mountaineer-gear-sale-to-take-place-at-gold-blue-spring-festival</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Mountaineer-Gear-Sale" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/8/852083108-fb26_gearsale_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. - The West Virginia University Athletics Department will conduct its sixth Mountaineer gear sale on Saturday, April 18, as part of the Gold-Blue Spring Festival from 9:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m., in the Diversified Energy Terrace club area of Milan Puskar Stadium.]]></description><med